---
title: Harissa Beef & Black Bean Couscous with Yoghurt
description: Harissa, the chilli-based condiment originating from North Africa varies in heat from mild to firey. Our version is definitely on
the mild side, with a gentle heat plus warming spices. It's the ideal sauce to complement beef, and with hearty couscous plus a
cooling yoghurt, this bowl is a burst of flavour in every bite!

*Unfortunately, this
week's chickpeas were
in short supply, so
we've replaced them
with black beans. Don't
worry, the recipe will
be just as delicious, just
be sure to follow your
recipe card!*
